# Backend Development (XForge)

TypeScript only. Governance: `skills/reference/architecture.md`, `AGENTS.md`. Security: `backend-security.mdc`.

## Next.js docs — MCP, not memory

`nextjs-docs://llms-index` → `nextjs_docs`. Dev server: `nextjs_index` → `nextjs_call`. See `nextjs-mcp-quality.mdc`.

## Execution layers (do not skip)

| Layer | Path | Responsibility |
|-------|------|----------------|
| Domain pipeline | `packages/features/**/src/actions.ts` | `createExecutionPipeline` / `createQueryPipeline` — auth, tenant, company, Zod, permission, domain op, audit |
| Feature API | `packages/features/**/src/server.ts` | Public server exports; apps import `/server` only |
| App runtime | `apps/app/app/**/_execution.ts` | `resolveRuntimeTenantAccess`, permission pre-checks, inject `postCommitHooks` |
| UI entry | `apps/app/**/actions.ts` | Parse FormData → call app `_execution` → cache/UI refresh |
| External HTTP | `apps/app/**/route.ts`, `apps/api` | Webhooks and third-party callbacks only |

```typescript
// apps/app — thin action; pipeline owns auth/audit
'use server'

import { updateTag } from 'next/cache'
import { createCustomerForTenant } from '@/app/api/customers/_execution'

export async function createCustomerAction(formData: FormData) {
  const customer = await createCustomerForTenant(/* parsed body */)
  updateTag('customers') // read-your-own-writes (Server Actions only)
  return customer
}
```

## `createExecutionPipeline` order (fixed)

`packages/execution/pipeline.ts` runs hooks in this order — do not reorder or bypass:

1. `requireAuth` → 2. `resolveActiveTenant` → 3. `requireTenantMembership` → 4. `resolveActiveCompany` (optional) → 5. `requireCompanyGrant` (optional) → 6. `validateInput` → 7. `requirePermission` → 8. `executeDomainOperation` (+ audit write) → 9. `postCommitHooks` (after success only)

Sensitive reads: `createQueryPipeline` with the same scope/permission gates.

## Post-commit and cache (no separate rule)

**`postCommitHooks`** — side effects after audit succeeds: notifications, external sync, search indexing. Pass from app `_execution.ts`. Hooks use `Promise.allSettled`; keep idempotent.

**Cache invalidation** — not in domain ops or pre-audit code:

| API | Where | When |
|-----|-------|------|
| `updateTag` | Server Actions only | User must see their write immediately |
| `revalidateTag` | Actions or Route Handlers | Stale-while-revalidate OK |
| `revalidatePath` | Actions or Route Handlers | Route-wide refresh; prefer tags |
| `refresh()` | Server Actions | Client router UI only — not tag revalidation |

Tagged reads: `cacheTag` inside `"use cache"` helpers with `cacheLife`. Extract helpers — never `"use cache"` inline in route handler bodies. MCP path: `/docs/app/getting-started/revalidating`.

## Server Actions vs Route Handlers

- **Server Actions** — in-app mutations and forms
- **Route Handlers** — webhooks, external HTTP; never colocate `route.ts` with `page.tsx`
- Route handlers that mutate must still delegate business logic to feature `/server` → pipeline

## Anti-patterns

```typescript
// ❌ DB write in app action — no pipeline, no audit
await db.delete(users).where(eq(users.id, id))

// ❌ Cache before mutation succeeds
updateTag('customers')
await createCustomerForTenant(body)

// ❌ Integration side effect inside executeDomainOperation
await syncToExternalCRM(customer) // belongs in postCommitHook

// ✅ Pipeline + post-commit + cache after success
const customer = await createCustomerForTenant(body)
updateTag('customers')
```

